<%- include("partials/header") %>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Great Scientists</title>
    <!-- Add Bootstrap CSS -->
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>

<!-- Main Content -->
<div class="container mt-4">
    <h1>Welcome to Great Scientists</h1>
    <p>Explore the lives and contributions of some of history's greatest scientists.</p>

    <!-- Isaac Newton -->
    <div id="newton" class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h2>Isaac Newton</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>Isaac Newton (1643-1727) was an English physicist, mathematician, and astronomer. He is widely regarded as one of the most influential scientists in history. Newton is best known for his work in physics, especially his laws of motion and universal gravitation.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Albert Einstein -->
    <div id="einstein" class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h2>Albert Einstein</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>Albert Einstein (1879-1955) was a German-born theoretical physicist who later became a naturalized American citizen. Einstein is famous for his theory of relativity, including the equation E=mcÂ².</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Marie Curie -->
    <div id="curie" class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h2>Marie Curie</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>Marie Curie (1867-1934) was a pioneering physicist and chemist. She discovered the elements polonium and radium and conducted pioneering studies on the properties of radioactive materials.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Charles Darwin -->
    <div id="darwin" class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h2>Charles Darwin</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>Charles Darwin (1809-1882) was an English naturalist and biologist known for his contributions to the theory of evolution. His most famous work, "On the Origin of Species," introduced the theory of natural selection.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>

